<qti-assessment-item xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0" xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" identifier="Q19_v11" title="Radicales - barras metálicas" time-dependent="false" adaptive="false" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0 https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/schema/xsd/imsqti_asiv3p0_v1p0.xsd">
  <qti-response-declaration identifier="RESPONSE" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier">
    <qti-correct-response>
      <qti-value>ChoiceB</qti-value>
    </qti-correct-response>
  </qti-response-declaration>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SOLUTION" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SCORE" cardinality="single" base-type="float">
    <qti-default-value>
      <qti-value>0</qti-value>
    </qti-default-value>
  </qti-outcome-declaration>
  <qti-item-body>
    <qti-choice-interaction response-identifier="RESPONSE" shuffle="false" max-choices="1">
      <qti-prompt>
        Un fabricante corta barras metálicas de longitud
        <m:math>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mn>2</m:mn>
            <m:msqrt>
              <m:mn>5</m:mn>
            </m:msqrt>
          </m:mrow>
        </m:math>
        metros cada una. Para armar una estructura, se utilizan 3 barras idénticas alineadas. Un estudiante escribe la longitud total como
        <m:math>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mn>3</m:mn>
            <m:mo>·</m:mo>
            <m:mn>2</m:mn>
            <m:msqrt>
              <m:mn>5</m:mn>
            </m:msqrt>
          </m:mrow>
        </m:math>
        metros.
        ¿Cuál es la expresión simplificada que representa la longitud total de las 3 barras?
      </qti-prompt>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceA">
        <m:math>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mn>6</m:mn>
            <m:msqrt>
              <m:mn>25</m:mn>
            </m:msqrt>
          </m:mrow>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceA" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. La longitud total es 3 · 2√5 = (3 · 2)√5 = 6√5. En esta opción, 6√25 = 6 · 5 = 30, y 30 es distinto de 6√5.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceB">
        <m:math>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mn>6</m:mn>
            <m:msqrt>
              <m:mn>5</m:mn>
            </m:msqrt>
          </m:mrow>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceB" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">¡Correcto! La longitud total es 3 · 2√5 = (3 · 2)√5 = 6√5, que coincide exactamente con esta expresión.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceC">
        <m:math>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mn>3</m:mn>
            <m:msqrt>
              <m:mn>10</m:mn>
            </m:msqrt>
          </m:mrow>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceC" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. La longitud total es 3 · 2√5 = 6√5. Además, 3√10 no es igual a 6√5, porque si fueran iguales, al dividir por 3 se tendría √10 = 2√5, y al cuadrar ambos lados resultaría 10 = 20, lo cual es falso.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceD">
        <m:math>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mn>5</m:mn>
            <m:msqrt>
              <m:mn>5</m:mn>
            </m:msqrt>
          </m:mrow>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceD" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. La longitud total es 3 · 2√5 = (3 · 2)√5 = 6√5. Esta opción propone 5√5, y 5√5 es distinto de 6√5 porque cambia el coeficiente de 6 a 5.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
    </qti-choice-interaction>
    <qti-feedback-block identifier="show" outcome-identifier="SOLUTION" show-hide="show">
      <qti-content-body>
        <p><strong>Resolución paso a paso</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 1: Identificar la longitud de una barra</strong></p>
            <p>Cada barra mide:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                  <m:msqrt>
                    <m:mn>5</m:mn>
                  </m:msqrt>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
              metros.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 2: Multiplicar por la cantidad de barras</strong></p>
            <p>Como se utilizan 3 barras idénticas alineadas, la longitud total es:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>3</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>·</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                  <m:msqrt>
                    <m:mn>5</m:mn>
                  </m:msqrt>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 3: Simplificar el producto</strong></p>
            <p>Se multiplican los números que están fuera del radical:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>3</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>·</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                  <m:msqrt>
                    <m:mn>5</m:mn>
                  </m:msqrt>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                    <m:mn>3</m:mn>
                    <m:mo>·</m:mo>
                    <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                    <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:msqrt>
                    <m:mn>5</m:mn>
                  </m:msqrt>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>6</m:mn>
                  <m:msqrt>
                    <m:mn>5</m:mn>
                  </m:msqrt>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 4: Comparar con las alternativas</strong></p>
            <p>La expresión simplificada obtenida es:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>6</m:mn>
                  <m:msqrt>
                    <m:mn>5</m:mn>
                  </m:msqrt>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>Esta coincide con la alternativa B.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Conclusión</strong></p>
            <p>La expresión simplificada que representa la longitud total de las 3 barras es:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>6</m:mn>
                  <m:msqrt>
                    <m:mn>5</m:mn>
                  </m:msqrt>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
              metros.
            </p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </qti-content-body>
    </qti-feedback-block>
  </qti-item-body>
  <qti-response-processing>
    <qti-response-condition>
      <qti-response-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SCORE">
          <qti-base-value base-type="float">1</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else>
    </qti-response-condition>
  </qti-response-processing>
</qti-assessment-item>